          <h2>Alan Anderson</h2>
          <p class="lead mb-0">My name is Alan Anderson, born and raised in San Diego, CA. For the first 18 years of my life I was an overweight individual, who lived everyday eating junk food and playing video games. Through high school I worked my way up to 274 lbs. and decided that I would no longer live my life this way. I than began my fitness journey; I found a personal trainer, poured money, time & commitment into it and within 8 months I had lost 91 lbs. (274-183lbs.)
I am a firm believer that anyone who has the right people around them and the right belief in self can accomplish anything. I was not born into this world fit and active, I had and continue to work on it everyday of my life. I understand the hardship, changes and challenges that have to be made in order to achieve your goals and dreams.
<br>
I have a few standards I require in every class from each athlete. I do not demand perfection but good hard work. My top priority in every class is safety. I have a strong passion for getting all athletes to move to the best of their ability, always striving to hit their true potential. It is my experience and belief that if you can constantly move well you will not only increase you athletic ability, you will also increase your ability to stay fit and ready for the rigors and unknowns of every day life. I am always looking for new ways to make class a learning experience, but more importantly I am always striving to make the class fun!
<br>
Credentials:
NASM CPT
NASM CES
CrossFit Level 2 Coach
CrossFit Olympic Lifting
CrossFit Powerlifting
CrossFit Gymnastics
CrossFit Movement and Mobility
SPEAR PDR Certified Coach
<br>
Hobbies:
I love to surf, shoot firearms, learn, workout, hang with friends & play chess. </p>
        </div>
