I have always been active. I grew up doing gymnastics and figure skating. I later got certified as a personal trainer and started teaching bootcamps. I had a friend tell me about Crossfit, and I tried it and never want to leave this sport. I love the community and family aspect of it. I love strategizing my workouts and mentally pushing myself beyond what I ever thought that I could do. I love being strong and being around strong and likeminded people. Getting the opportunity to coach this sport that I love so much is amazing, and I am very grateful. I love when people say that they can’t do something because I will change it to something that they can do. I love building rapports with the members and really helping them move well, in addition to making them love where they come to work hard everyday.
<br>
I love weightlifting, but my speciality is more the gymnastics side. I love all the handstands and different variations, and all the muscle ups. When I’m not at the gym, I’m probably thinking about the gym, but I enjoy hiking and riding my bike around the beach, music, going out with friends, trying new food, and hanging with my dog. I enjoy being outside with good people and anywhere their is live music. I live to explore. It’ll be 4 years in March that I have been doing CrossFit and I wouldn’t change it for the world.
<br>
Certifications include:
CF L1
NCSF
Nesta </p>
